Ask HN: As these AI models get better, how do we continue to live?
text:
I'm absolutely loving the technological progress that I'm seeing with these models. It feels like I'm living in the future and I'm excited for whats to come. I also feel like its only a matter of time until I lose my job.

I work in a somewhat technical field and I'm pretty sure an AI could easily do 60% of my job. I chose a job that has low stress and great work life balance instead of doing something more challenging and I don't regret it. I've built a life outside of work that I'm very content with it.

Despite all this, we unfortunately live in a society where you need to work to live. I can't sustain myself on my hobbies nor do I have any interest in doing so. So what can we do right now to prepare? I'm sure government intervention will be necessary but I'm doubtful that they're even capable of understanding exactly what is happening and how big of a deal it is.

Ask HN: Get base64 PNG image out of ChatGPT
text:
I come to you HN with a curiosity. The other day I was playing with ChatGPT to make HTML code. Then I had a thought: "what if I ask ChatGPT to give me png base64 binary in an img tag?" I wanted to view it in the browser. Would it be an actual image?

So far my attempts have be futile. ChatGPT understands the idea, but what it outputs is either reduced like

<img src="data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAA..." alt="Company logo">

Or it gets too big, which I think hits some kind of max response size limit. Putting that code in an HTML file gives a `net::ERR_INVALID_URL`.

And finally, I know what Dalle2 is, in case you were wondering.
